verbose_text: Non-insulin-dependent glucose uptake by the tumor, reflected in hyperlactacidemia, is often found in these cases and may also contribute to hypoglycemia.12 The metabolic alterations caused by NICTH are reversible after surgical removal of the big-IGF-2-producing tumor,13 although metabolic disturbances usually relapse.12, 14 In the current case, neither the patient 's liver enzymes, bilirubin, nor International Normalized Ratio were elevated, and she did not have any liver metastases.
